        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=43285&amp;TOPIC_ID=5370&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=How+do+you+organize+your+spell+book%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Page 1 and 2 - Spells I swap out most often. Arch Lich, FD, HS, Sheild of Magi, DMF, Manaskin, HP Pact, Twitch.</P><P>Page 3 and 4 - Damage DOTs, life taps, DD.</P><P>Page 5 and 6 - Offensive control spells. Various darknesses, roots, Insidious Retrogression, Invoke Fear, ST, undead slow, undead charm.</P><P>Page 7 and 8 - Travel related spells. Gate, Bind affinty, Skin of Shadow, Breath of the Dead, Invis to Undead. </P><P>Page 9 and 10 - Misc not often used spells. Shadow Step, resist buffs, cures, Chilling Embrace, Sacrifice, Convergence.</P><P>Page 11 and 12 - Blank.</P><P>Page 13 and up - Left over spells, organized by level and then alphebetically.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

