        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well for a very long time I managed to keep it pretty well organized.  I use page 1&2 for my top 10 spells, and pages 3&4 for the next 10 most used spells.  Pages 5&6 for debuffs and crowd control, and pages 7&8 for heals and pets.  Page 10 is buffs that I don't cast all the time.  Page 20 is utility spells that I only mem once in a while, like gate and bind.  Retired spells go to the back, roughly organized by icon.</P><P>That's how I used to do it.  In the last few spell ranks I've just gotten lazy or sloppy, so I now have spells all over the place.  Going to have to fix that one day soon.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22254" target="_blank">Sssyx Syxyx</a><BR><a href="http://eqmoonies.freeservers.com">Spirit of the Moon</a></P><P><a href="mailto:sssyx@mmdog.com">sssyx@mmdog.com</a></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
