         i used to keep my pages in level order with 1 page full of spells from random levels that i used.  recently i rearranged my book to keeping like spells with each other.  page 1 being all of my normal line ups...low level spells and spells i never use are just stored on the last pages of my spell book.  but aside from that...undead spells are together (charm, DD's, slows), darkness' are together, DoTs, DD's, group spells (the taps, heals, etc...), etc...</P><P>it has taken me a bit to get used to this setup from my old one though ,hehe.</P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

